   (3) 💬 1. **Audited stale checkboxes** — found and verified three items already implemented by earlier commits but still marked open (pointer-enter hover-bridge fix, embeddable-component manifest shape, popup content sizing/reposition), updated `todo.md` with citations.
   (3) 💬 
   (3) 💬 2. **Implemented the one genuinely open item**: popup buffer padding + input-region masking for shadows. Popover popup buffers were sized exactly to content, clipping any `box-shadow`/`filter` overshoot (including from descendant nodes like floating bubble buttons), and no Wayland input region was set for popups. Fixed by extracting a shared shadow/filter-overflow helper from the existing damage-rect code, computing per-popover padding across the whole subtree, inflating the popup buffer/positioner accordingly (with offset compensation so visible content stays anchored), and restricting the input region to the true content rect — mirroring the existing parent-surface tooltip pattern.
